\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Can you give me your full name Mr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912 .}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912  Harry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 William Thomas Harry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Tremayne, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Tolver Place{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Penzance{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You were married and are now a widower?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes. Married in - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Montreal{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What year were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 '96. 1896.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Trewellard Hill, Pendeen. Wheal Bal Hil
l it's called, Wheal Bal Hill, Wheal Bal. It's - that's the name of the place, Wheal Bal Hill. Pen - Pendeen. Mm. In the parish of St Just. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 How many years did you live in the house in which you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh four I think - as far as I know, 
my father came home from the Boer - Boer War and - went to live in Carnyorth, all my childhood was spent at a village called Carnyorth. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Is that near to Pendeen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes - it's between Pendeen and - yes, about a mile from where - less than a mile.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Less than a mile from Pendeen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 From - yes, and from where I was born.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 In the same parish of St Just?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? Yes, oh yes, yes, oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 How long did you live at Carnyorth then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 From - 1900 to - until I joined the army in 19 - August 1914.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You joined the army at the outbreak of war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, three weeks after, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And your parents continued to live at Carnyorth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, my father was in South Africa then. At Randfontein.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 He came home from the Boer War in 1900 and how long before he went to South Africa?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Oh he went over to South Africa again in 19 - 1902, and - came back - in six months. But he had something like the - Tuckingmill - stream, they had a - a lot of water was down in Kenidjack Valle
y near St Just, and they used to crush the ore from all over the - old mines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 He worked there when he came home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, he was a partner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was in 1900 to 1902?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 To 1910.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 But he went out to South Africa?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Again 1910. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you say he went to South Africa two years after he came home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Six months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And came back again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And that was when he acquired the interest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, he acquired the interest in 19 - in 1900. He was still a partner when he went out there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 When he went to South Africa would he have gone under his own steam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Would there have been any particular reason for going at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, I don't think so. More than that he - he - he were a bit roaming.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 He had itchy feet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 He came - pardon, at that time, yes it seems. I don't know of any other reason. Price of tin was down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 If the price of tin was down it might be that he would be better off going to South Africa?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well he thought so but he came home a sick man. He was up at Barbiton then. In Northern Transvall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And he just stayed six months?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 He came home again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And resumed his partnership.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 In this Tuckingmill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. The Symbler, I said they used to cru
sh the ore down in the village in the - valley down - north of St Just, Nancherrow Valley, where they had lots of water wheels. I said similar to - to - mm. No, the old - mine dumps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Working them over?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Working the old mine dumps, yes, and - tran
sporting them by cart. If you listen to that other - thing, you - after you've done this you can rectify anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you have any brothers or sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Six. Three brothers and three sisters - eventually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Could you tell me the name of the eldest?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And then who was next?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh I had a sister next.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What was her name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Mary Ann. Well you want the - all my - names of all my family? Well what's that for? Can I remember, of course I can remember, yes. Well I had three brothers and three sisters you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You were the eldest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Your sister was next?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Was she a year or two years younger than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, she was born 1900. Actually I suppose my father came home in '99 I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And she was born in 1900?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Who was next to her then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 My - another sister, in 1902. Then a brother 19 -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What was her Christian name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Dorothy May. Good God, what are they asking all this for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Who next then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Then I had a brother Raymond. He wrote a little book here called the Mine Under the Sea. Read it out. Mm. Well that's him, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And Raymond would be perhaps another two years younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, wait a minute. Hang on a bit, you've got Mildred. Mildred died - when she was fourteen in 1919. She was born 1905 wasn't she?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 She was younger than Raymond?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. Yes, younger than Raymond, yes, but I think she was younger than Richard too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So Raymond and then Mildred.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And - yes, I think so, and then Richard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And he's the one that wrote the Mine Under the Sea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, Raymond. Then Henry. Aye, he's live at - he - he's working over at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912 
- on the staff of the Unigate o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 r at
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That's the creameries?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mm. Rich - Richard is dead. Mildred is dead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So I've got Dorothy, Raymond, Mildred, Richard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Annie. Mary Anne you've got haven't you? Well I told you she - my sister was born in 1900, Mary Anne I said. Did - did you miss that?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was next to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes. Two years after, just after - I - Mary Anne - Annie she were called. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Dorothy - is Mildred next?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, I suppose. No, Dorothy, Raymond was next I - I - I told you, Raymond was next.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Raymond?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mildred I think. Pardon? Dorothy was before Raymond.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And after Raymond?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Was Mildred. I - I think so. Mm. Yes, that would be it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You were the eldest, your father, did he also come from the St Just district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes. He - he and my mother came from about half mile away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 How old would he have been when you were born would you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
He was forty-three when he died - with silicosis. He - he was born '76. So he'd bet twenty-four would - twenty - twenty-one. Twenty - seventy, no, he wasn't, he was born '74. '74. My mother was born in '76. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And he came from the same area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And his occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Miner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Would that have been underground?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 'Course - he was a mine captain out in South Africa for five years before he came home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And he always worked as a miner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, he was working on these dumps for ten years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was after he'd been abroad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well he was abroad three times. In 1910 they had to quit all this job, and he went abroad again. In 1910 he went abro
ad again and I didn't see him anymore. Never, because when I - when he came home I - I was overseas, in the army. And he died before I came home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So he went to South Africa in 1910?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And when did he come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 '15. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 After you had gone off to the war?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 His first work would have been mining after he left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, he was working in Levant, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 In Levant mine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
was the mine that was flooded?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 The same mine as I started}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Do you remember your father ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. He wasn't that type, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Your mother came from the same area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 He went away the last time because - there was no hope of - keeping - a family of seven - and I think he was - ke
en to - well he couldn't bring 'em up as he wanted to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Why would that have been at that stage in 1910, would it have been because of lack of employment in St Just?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. Lack of employment, he was - they - they were partnership. It - it was becaus
e the - the Lord - stopped all mineral rights. They wouldn't allow them to have any more dumps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Who was the owner of the mineral rights then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh Lord Falmouth I suppose. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 He said no more working of dumps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 His agent. But what do they want to know this for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well it's family background and area background as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well it's all on my reel there you know. I see. And it's in that paper - those papers you had. All right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did mother work before she was married?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I - I think she - put her time as a mill - milliner would it be. Hat maker isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was possible in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did she work after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. Had too many children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 In this house at Carnyorth where you lived most of your childhood, could you tell me how many rooms there would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Eight. Two room - two houses made into one. Made into one. My father spent a lot of money on that - at odd times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 He modernized it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, very - mm. But there was no running water nor no indoor sanitation you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 How many bedrooms would there have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Three. And a - and - and a spare room, if you like. Four - four really, but there was no bed in the fourth one. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And a reception room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Four rooms downstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What we would have called a front room or parlour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Yes, and - and a front room, parlour and - and a front room they called it. A kitchen and a big pantry. And a pantry. And - and two - outside, coal house, outside wash house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did anyone else besides your parents and brothers and sisters live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No other relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? Oh - occasionally. She did more - yes. Yes, very little - very - I should say no if I was going to be asked I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Spring cleaning time or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, and papering and things like that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Special efforts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And we all had to work as we grew - grew up and especially me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 In the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Yes. Like - like - carrying the water and - turning the handle of the washing machine in those days and - cleaning the knives and spoons and forks and I would work like the devil.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Thos were duties that you had to do, did any of the other children have to do that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 My eldest sister, Annie, yes. She later went to a private school up at St. Just.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 She would do the domestic chores just like you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes. Everybody had to do something - with my mother. And my two younger brothers came in here to a private school. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did mother or father make any of the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 The what? No, not - they were - they - they used to engage a - seamstress who - who -
 there - they used to carry around a machine in those days, dressmakers and - tailors and that - seamstress, they used to be - used to come out and work at your house for about a shilling a day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Someone like that used to come and make clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes, but the other - the suits and that for me came from tailors.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 But this would be mainly for underclothes and the girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, I don't think so. Just odd jobs that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mending?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Making curtain perhaps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes - I - I think they used to make perhaps dresses for some of the sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Shoes would be bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 In Pensance probably?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well, of course the - men's boots and that used to be made by local shoemakers. They were very - very very skilled men.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Was there a shoemaker in St Just?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? Two - three, three or four, yes. Yes. Oh yes, that was a skilled trade in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 St Just at that stage would have been }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912 m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 ore of a town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Probably as big as Penzance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. No, no. Never. Never, no. No never. Not - not in living memory, I mean, not - may back a hundred and twenty years perhaps it was.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Would there be any people making shoes in St Just now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, I think there's someone there named Curnow, I - I think there's one up there, I'm not sure. I believe there's one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 The lady who came to do the sewing would be a local woman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 She was a - she was a deformed little woman. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Carried her own sewing machine?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Carried her own machine, very crippled little woman. I often wish I helped her a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Was she married, have a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. Deformed little woman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Nowadays men and women help each other to do domestic work, in those days would your father have helped with any of the work in the home?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 On Sundays when he was - yes, when he was home he used to - prepare the vegetables and all that sort of thing, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 He prepared vegetables and helped mother generally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, when he was home - on Sunday. He was a good man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What about - you told me that he modernized these cottages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Would he have done that himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. Had his brother-in-law. Spent a lot of money there. It was the best house in the village. Mm. Then we had a front garden put 
up in front of the house and - we had a nice back garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What was grown in the gardens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? Yes, all the - all - all the household vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 To feed the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Of course it didn't feed a family but I mean it helped a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 But Cornish gardens mostly were for fathers to grow the vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh yes. Yes, yes. Yes, they used to be very proud of what they used to grow in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So besides decorating he would have done some gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did he take any hand in helping with you children, like putting you to bed?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh I don't know. No, I - I don't think so, he never interfered in that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That would have been mother's job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. I think he would be told to keep out if he did. Imagine so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Would he have told you stories and read to you and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
No. My mother did when he was abroad. Yes. She died only a year - two or three years ago, she was ninety-one. She went very very deaf which was a - a family complaint. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It's a wonderful age though isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. She had three brothers who died before they were thirty-two with silicosis and - South Africa.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 They all went to South Africa?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, they - the eldest one was only thirty-five. And - he came home from Tasmania.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Underground miners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Is this recording all this time? Oh my word.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You've told me about the tasks you had to carry out yourself, the cleaning of the silver and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 How long did you continue to do these little home jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 After I was working in Levant - in Levant, yes, on Monday - Mad Mondays, you know the old Cornish -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 When mother had the washing to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, and I had to turn the damned handle you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That would be the handle of the?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Washing machine that used to bob up and down you know. You haven't seen one perhaps? Oh the - the inside of the - thing was all - like a washboard you know, rough, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912 serrated}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 , and the - this plunger used to plunge up and down as you turned the handle, it - it had a cover on you know. A - a - a hand washing machine. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I've never seen one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh well - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I've seen the old mangle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh yes, we - they used to use those, yes. Great long things from here to the
 stove. We had a - we had a - a mangle put in our - we had a mangle put in the house for my mother. Mm. And she used to bake the home bread too you know. Yes. Good bread too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Your sister next to you, she helped with these jobs in the home and all the others also did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
No, not so much I don't think, I - no, my younger brother was only five when I went away, and he came in here to school and my - my two younger brothers came in here - to a private school in Penzance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you have to help with the younger ones, like seeing them to school or dressing them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
No, no, no. No. No, I used to go to Pendeen a mile away to a night school every night when I came home. And Saturday nights I used to go down to Botallack to a school, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 More or less, yes. But I had to - you mean young or when I was fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 In your schooldays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh my schooldays, oh, even then I - I started going to a night school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What time would you have gone to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh - I - I - used to go to bed you know with a candle, candlestick you know, no oil lamps. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Any reading in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Not enough light?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. Not normally. We were too tired then. And kids didn't care read in bed, you weren't allowed to with your mother very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You wouldn't have been allowed to read in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Not very often, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Do you remember mother putting you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Always on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Yes. I wasn't the favourite really I suppose I - my mother, I always - always used to consider that my mother was - very hard on me, but I suppose it's really because you're the eldest, you've got to - take the brunt of everything you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You had to share the responsibility with her probably?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, not responsibility my God no. My mother was a - a - a disciplinarian in that way. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 There were six of you children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You had to share the bedroom with your brothers I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Oh yes, I think so. 'Cos one was usually so small he was always in a cot in the bedroom. And - the damn thing - I said in my book here they started coming along pretty fast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Every two years or year and a half wouldn't it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 The one thing t
hat - in my - later experience which - affected me most was that they'd cut out grammar in the school curriculum. And when I was commissioned to the Indian Army and had to learn - Hindustani and all that I had to get a book - \{BLANK\}
 grammar, and when I've travel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
ed in Spain and Central Africa and - Malaya and Siam and - and Rhodesia - and all those places - South America, Colombia and Venezuela, I've always - found that the lan - the loss of - grammar in the day school was the biggest stumbling block that I had.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I've heard that mentioned by other people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? Have you? Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It's a great luck really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Always together. And talking wasn't allowed. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You all ate in the big family kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Yes. 'Course the - you've got to remember that when children are very young they didn't - they weren't always seven sitting round the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You'd have meals at different times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, no, no, 'course they were young -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Some would be in the high chair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So you ate in the large kitchen living room or dining room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Only in the dining room when - had visitors. Or Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So you used the dining room on high days and holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, and for study, I used to study in there. In the - front room. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And it would be used at Christmas when all the family ate together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Oh the family was always there of course. But - I never saw my father after - I was at day sc
hool when he went away. He was a good man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Do you feel you missed a lot by your father being away in those years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. I missed a lot - more ways than one too. 'Cos he was always }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912 \endash 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912  help}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
in me and - even when he was away with my - buying - if I w
anted a technical book and my mother wouldn't let me have it. I'd write out to him and he'd say you get it. She didn't see the value of education like - he did. She's a good woman. Her - her - but - everyone used to say how clean the - the - they all went
 to chapel on Sunday and all that, they were always kept clean. Beautifully clean.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Where did mother do her cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 In the kitchen. On a Cornish slab.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 A Cornish range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No gas or electricity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, no, no, no. No, no. No, only oil lamp at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 When was breakfast eaten, was it all the family together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, not normally I don't think. 'Cos you got to remember the family was growing up all the time you see, they wouldn't all -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 When you had breakfast what other members of the family would be present, I suppose those closest to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Thos closest to you would have been going to school and having breakfast at the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes. Yes, I suppose so, I don't remember much now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What would breakfast normally consist of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Coo, I don't know now, we always had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Porridge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Egg and things like that. I don't know what else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Bread and butter I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh yes - yes, and of course pilchards were store - w
ere - were - pilchards were bought then you see and about six a penny, five and six a penny you see. And - other fish sometimes used to come - be brought round in a cart from Newlyn you know. You see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Would fish have been eaten at breakfast time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Not that I'm aware of. I don't know, I don't think so. You have what you call a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912 scrawled}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912  pilchards but - yes, sometimes for tea. Look is that - not running out yet is it? Stop itself will it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you have anything special on certain days like Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh always had - yes, special meal on Sundays, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That would have been a special dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, lunch, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You've told me that mother baked her own bread, did she make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 All sorts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. And she made the best blackberry wine I've ever tasted. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did she make any other wines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. But people around did, plenty of 'em around used to make all kinds of wines like they do now. Rhubarb and - and parsnip and all
 - dandelion, all this - nonsense which - I never touch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mother made parsnip and dandelion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Only the blackberry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Redberry sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did she bottle any fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, I don't think so. I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Do you remember if she made any pickles?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh yes, plenty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Onions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Any other kind of pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I don't know - she used to pickle pears and apples. And she used to salt down pilchards. And butter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Salt the butter when it was cheapest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Cheap, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 How did she do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Put it in a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912 bursa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912  as we call it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 One of those tall earthenware jars?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So she salted down pilchards in that and butter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did she make any wine or medicines for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
No. No - oh - no, you always had a - if you had a cold you had to have - elderberry in those days, hold your - face over a - a basin of elderberry and poisoned you nearly. I used to hate it like the devil.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It was good for colds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 They said so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Any beer brewed for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
No, no, my - my father was teetotal. I never knew him to go into a pub. He never interfered with the other men but - I never knew him smoke or go into a pub.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 He was teetotal and didn't smoke?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. He wasn't a stiff man but he was a good man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You told me that he grew vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Was any fruit grown?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. Gooseberries, yes. Yes. No, nothing -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No blackcurrants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, my granny did. And we ate them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mother would have made gooseberry jam I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. No, we never had enough I don't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 They were eaten for tart and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes, yes, that's right, that's quite right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Would they have bought vegetables out of season?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Yes, if - well the greengrocers used to come round you see regularly, but I used to - lead around an old - blind man who used to come selling tea, he got blinded in the mine, there were several fellows around who'd been blinded in the mine
, there were several fellows around who'd been blinded in the mine, and this old chap used to carry - tea, and I used to take him over the banks and this, that and the other sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So after he was blinded he set up this vegetable round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, tea. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you say that somebody on the vegetable round had also been injured in the mine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. No. The pilchards used to be brought round in a cart you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mother would buy those and salt them down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did she dry them in any way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? Oh marinated pilchards sometimes. Yes. I - I didn't like those either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Marinated is what I think the north country people call soused.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Call what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It's pickled in vinegar really isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pilchards, yes, and - and cloves and - bay leaf.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That's what the north country people call soused I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 We call it marinated?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 My aunt used to dry pilchards on a rod outside of her door.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, oh yes, well that's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912 scrawl}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912  pilchard we call it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912 Scrawled}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912  - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912 scrawled}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912  - used to dry them and then put them on the fire you see, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912 scrawl}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912 Scrawl}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
. Yes. Put 'em on a - grid iron. Yes, lovely things. Don't see them now do you. Yes. It was shoved in the fire - shoved in the fireplace there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
then it would simply drip the fat into the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, that's right, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did they ever buy tinned vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? Skinned vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Tinned. Nothing tinned in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. No, no, no, you didn't see tins in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did they keep any livestock for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Chicken. Yes, down on the green - the common - common -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 In your garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, no, down on the common - outside the houses, some undivided land you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912  
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912 Common}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912  land?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes, about fifty yards in front of the - all the houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What would be the local name for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 For what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 For that common land?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh no, it's just out in front of the houses at Carnyorth, it was Carnyorth. There were lots of old }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912 craals}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 , t
hese old - houses constructed of great big rocks where the old people - a - a hundred years ago, and they've - they've all gone now, they've all fallen down now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Their houses would have been built of the rocks that they'd dug?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 The granite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That they'd dug out of the soil?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I suppose so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 They would clear the soil of rocks and build the houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I - I suppose so, they were built many many years before my time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 They were derelict when you were a boy were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Occupied?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 All of them. Place full of miners then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Occupied mostly by miners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 All miners. Every house was occupied. Yes, every house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 These fowls wandered on the communal land outside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 How would you know yours from somebody else's?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
you always knew that. Well yes, you'd go down with your - with your grain and you'd drive off all the others. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you have any hand in looking after those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, of course. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It was one of your little jobs was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Collecting eggs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Would you have to get them in at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. And shut them in, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 In your own property?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. If I saw a policeman down talking to my father - on a Sunday or any other time when he was a
t home, feeding the chicken, I used to be scared to go in from my granny's, I was scared of a - policeman and always with in trouble with them you know. We used to throw stones down the old shafts you see. Hear them rattle down there and all that, and the
n they'd come and - and - policeman come after you, go like the devil you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You would be breaking the law by doing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I suppose so. Set fire to all the bushes down in the moor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That would be fun?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well it was to us, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mischief?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Yes, mischief, yes, plenty of that round. 'Course miners always used to play marbles and - throw dice - throw - spears they call it, throw darts in the shoemakers shop. You see, all the places of congregation - the congregating then were - the
 shoemakers shop, there was one or two local institutes, but shoemakers shop was the general - places, or standing up by the corner of a house.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was the social focal point?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh yes. Yes, there was no - there was no social life -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You didn't keep any pigs or goats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. Good God, no, no,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Any meat you would buy at the butchers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 The butcher used to come round - with a cart. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Every day or once or twice a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Every day up - until Friday I think. Fri - I don't think he came Saturdays or Mondays, not to our place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So you would have had meat every day to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? Yes, oh yes, pretty well, yes, yes, every day, yes, unless it was fish or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And fish was plentiful and you could get it easily?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I suppose so. 'Course as a youth you don't worry about those things you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And you don't necessarily recall it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Ever have any rabbit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, only - but we - the first rabbit I had was in the army, when I was billeted in Bodmin, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No poaching went on in that area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, my father - used to - shoot a few birds in winter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What sort of birds would they be?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh well plover and that, things like that. Yes. Snipe if he could get 'em for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Where would he be able to shoot those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh around the moors. Places all for water there in winter time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That wouldn't be poaching anyway would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. No, not - no. Nothing there to poach.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It would be on the common land?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. And in the fields, yes. Oh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 There's large areas of common land there now aren't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Well not so much so now, most - a lot - Lord Falmouth got out of most of his things. You see, I - the house that we were in belonged to Lord Fa
lmouth, and he paid - when my father had put all that money on it he had it at nominal rent. Well I - I bought it for my mother - oh - over twenty years ago I suppose. Lord Falmouth sold because he had to pay nineteen and sixpence in the pound I believe, 
h
e sold all the villages, all everything. They were all built on the three lives system I believe. Person - they - when they started to build a house, in order to do that they had to nominate three lives in those days, and when the last life was gone the h
ouse fell over to the lords you know. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So it was a very uncertain period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Oh yes, very. Yes. My mother's - my grand - my mother's father, he - started - building a house and breaking in some land and it wasn't finished when they died and - the
y had to build it and pay rent for it. Oh the - believe me, the - working class in those days were - the lords - got all that's coming to them all right, I'm not a Labour man or anything like that but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 But that was the social condition of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
The social condition of the day was - yes, that if they built a house and they nominate three lives and there's - place down here now called Labour in Vain because - they were all dead before the place was finished. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Then the whole of it would go back to the Lord?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 To the Lords. And then you had to pay rent for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And in your case it was Lord Falmouth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. He - he owned most of the places around there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So the house when you were a lad and your father had it, your father rented it from Lord Falmouth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, yes, he spent a lot of money and he had nominal rent, and he had to keep it in repair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 There was no question of lives on it at that stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. No. No, no, oh no, Lord Falmouth - belonged to Lord Falmouth. 
It had - it - fell off the Lord Falmouth about - when I - suppose when I was about six, then two or three years after they went in it to live. That fell over to Lord Falmouth, and then that's the time he started pulling thing to pieces then. My uncle was 
the - head carpenter in Levant, and he used to come there and I had to hold a candle as a kid when I was about eight or}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
nine, six, seven, eight or nine, holding a candle 'til my arms used to ache, when he was doing the woodwork and all that. Yes, but it was a nice house after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 He was the carpenter, your father's brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes. My father's brother-in-law.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Your mother's brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. He married my mother's sister. His father was the manager of Levant one time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Most of the St Just people worked in the Levant mine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
At that time, the others were shut down then you see, the - they closed down around '96 a lot of them, but most of the mines in St Just closed down in '66, 1866. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What mine is it that's working there now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Geevor. Now that's taken in the Levant lease now but they aren't doing much. No. Levant's full of water down to - half floor as you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That's the mine under the sea?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 When you were growing up and your mother was looking after you
 all was there any evidence of her having to do without so that you could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Never was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, my father never - no - yes, my father was - yes. Oh no, no hardship of that kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You were fortunate in those days because there was a lot of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, well my father was a good man. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You told you weren't allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That applied to all of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. There was cane on table sometimes. Sometimes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Could you choose what you wanted to eat or did you have to have a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I don't know now, yes, you used to have what's on table. Yes. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Were your parents cross if you left food uneaten on your plate or did that never happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That wasn't usual.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You were good hungry healthy people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 If there was something on the table you wanted like the salt could you ask them to pass it to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, certainly yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You didn't have to wait until it was offered?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. Oh now, we had a - quite a - quite a - comfortable home, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Of course you could, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Were there any rulings about how you held your knife and fork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well you were supposed to be mannerly at table. Yes.
 That's the trouble, when I was commissioned you see I'd never used anything but a knife, fork and spoon, and when I got back to India and mixing with Army officers, public schoolboys - and two or three knives and forks and - the different - cutlery, I me
an I had to watch them. Which I did, kept my mouth shut. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 When you were a child could you bring anything to the table like toys or books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? When you asked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You would ask to leave?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You didn't have to wait until everybody was finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You said that all the family couldn't sit at table at the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well you see I mean even - in 1910 when my father went away - it's two or three - there was - two or three were only five, six years old.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you all have your own places at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Usually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 How was the meal served, by whom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 By my mother of course, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Any special order of serving?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. No, no. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Just went round the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Younger brothers and sisters, before they could feed themselves, they didn't sit at table then did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I - I - I couldn't - as far as I know they did, they were fed -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mother fed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. They had a spoon you see instead of a knife and fork.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mother didn't employ any servants did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? No. She - hadn't got any money for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Suppose you used to fight like other people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You used to fight a bit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I suppose so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did they say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh - oh be cowardly not to wouldn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Fight it out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I - I mean in the village nobody took - chi - parents didn't interfere in anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You fought your own battles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did your parents have any special ambitions for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. Go to work, that's all. My father - it's - always said - when I started to work he 
said - I could have gone in for teaching if - I'd wanted to but I want to travel. And I had a scholarship to go to Cambourne in 1914.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 To go to Camborne?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 School of Mines, yes. Yes. That's for going to night classes you see. After I came home fro
m work I used to go to night class - every night, and then I'd come back and study sometimes 'til midnight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 How did you get to Camborne then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 When?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 When you had to go to the School of Mines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well I - I had the scholarship in al - in 1914 and I went - ran away and joined the Army.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So you didn't take that up at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
No. And my mother wouldn't allow me - couldn't afford it they said. Anyway I didn't wait to find out, I - I joined the Army in August - August twenty-eighth nineteen fourteen. And I was away five years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Do you know what kind of people your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. No, I - I - no, those things are very different from social life today. Yes. Every - miner in the village in those days
 used to go to America or Africa or - somewhere like that, Australia, and lots of them didn't come back as you know. Same thing from Camborne and everywhere else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 They would emigrate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Was there any special means of emigrating do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Not that I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 They'd save enough money and go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
No, they had to borrow money in those days. Always borrow money, but if they borrow - my - I think my father borrowed thirty-five pounds - to go to Africa and he had to pay back sixty.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Who would he borrow it from, the bank?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh - from some - body who had it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Friend, relative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, some - well he - perhaps a little better - better off financially.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And they would feel that the person concerned was an honest person who would pay it back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Oh yes, they - you had to. Otherwise they wouldn't do it would they? But they used to make a lot of money like that, some used to lend fifty pound and get back a hundred. And some - some didn't get back at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 But that was the risk they took?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes. Oh yes, they had to borrow money to go away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And that was the way most of them managed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. My father, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What would your parents have thought of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I never heard my father swear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What about you, would you have been punished for swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I - I - I should think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 But it never happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. Told - keep quiet. No, that was one thing that
 you were not allowed to do. Was to interfere when - the elders were talking. Certainly not, not. Very strict that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 To take}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
part you would be asked to do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 If you did do something that your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Are you thinking - I - I remember telling a lie, and I wasn't allowed to go to Carbis Bay with the Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You were punished in that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You bet your life, yes. Yes. They -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was for telling a lie?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. And for - and for striving in it when I knew I was lying all the time I - I thought about it lots of times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You can remember that particular incident?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
yes, well you - you see you were headstrong, that's all. I went swimming when I was not allowed to. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So you were punished for doing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, I wasn't allowed to go away with the party that was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Whose decision was that, mother's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And my father. Yes. Both of 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You would learn that lesson then and not do that again I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I haven't been an a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 gel, not - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You can't think of any other incident where your parents would have punished you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, I never had a - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No corporal punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. No. No, I - no. Oh no, nothing like that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 How did you feel about being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh I don't know. Where - what you - as a child, what do you feel like? I mean, you - you forget about it again don't you? Yes. Yes.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Were you able to talk easily to your - mother as a young person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I couldn't say. She was very busy all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 She was strict?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 But if you had a problem could you have taken it to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I suppose so. She wasn't unreasonable. She was strict - but when you've got so many of them you know you've got - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So her showing of affection would have fitted in with her strict outlook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Yes. Oh yes, she used to - as I say, she - she - people used to pass remarks about the cleanliness of them all when they're going - being sent to chapel and Sunday school and all that. 'Course we had to go three times a day in those days. Three ti}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912 mes every Sunday. So }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
man full of religion that you don't go now you see. Mrs Warron goes Sunday nights. She - she's quite a - a - respectable woman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Would you say that
 you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents or did one play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, none, no, no. No. I - I think when you - when you go out into the world}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 you - your behaviour depends on yourself. I m
ean - the - your - your - environment when you're a child certainly plays an impart - important part but - as soon as you get big enough you - you - you use your own discretion and - I mean - I know I wrote to my father when he was in Africans - when I wa
s sixteen, I said, I'm going out to Michigan, he told me what he thought about it - in no uncertain terms. He said, you'll know when you leave home just what a home's like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was his experience?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, well I found it out to be my - my own too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 When you had a birthday would that be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, I don't think so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you receive any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Have any special treats to eat or guests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? No, not that I can - no. There were too many birthdays, we had too many birthdays. Seven of 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Can you remember anything you did with your mother and father together on Christmas day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, I don't think so. The Bands used to come round and play you see, the band used to come round and pl
ay carols and - if - if - there was a mason, I know my father didn't like - he had - he'd put one over him once and he used to put the lights out but they'd still come down and play outside the door. And if they did - and they played until the door was op
en.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 They would play}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 carols?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Outside the door?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. And the choirs would sing too you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Would they collect money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh yes. Always, that's what they came for, to - to tell you the truth. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you have any musical instruments in your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, I learnt the piano. Every - two years, yes, from 1908 to 1910 when I went to work in the mine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did any other members of the family play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes - all of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 The piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 All played the piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. All of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did anyone in the family sing?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did any of them sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well my elder sister was in a choir. But - I - I mean she wasn't soloist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 She was a choir member?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 At the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you ever make music or sing together at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
No. No, we used to hate damn piano just as much as - pardon me, but used to - hate practicing on the piano instead of out playing. I came - I came out and put the clock - fast because I was 
supposed to practise an hour, I didn't do it any more. You can imagine what happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So your music practice was really a bit of a chore?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, that's right, yes, I - when I trave}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 led after and on the ships going abroad and that I often wish I could play. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You regretted then not practising?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Yes. I did have a piano in my - marquee when I came back to India, in - I was in a Seihk regiment in Lahore, I did have a - I sent in an hired piano. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And you played it then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? They used to play ludo or something. Yes, that wasn't my father
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. I never had any time for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No cricket or anything on the green?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh there was plent
y of cricket on there, oh yes, everybody - oh that was the big thing - cricket matches. They used to come down even - from Troon you know when I was a boy. Come - miners meet out in South Africa and all that and arrange these cricket matches, they'd come 
down from as far as Troon down to St Just you know. That's in my book, that used to be a read letter day that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Of course your father was away until you were ten years old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 My father was away that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you say your father was away until you were ten years old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
No, I didn't. I said my father went away again in 1902, and he was away six months I said. And then he went away again 1910 when I was fourteen. Before I was fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So would he have played cricket with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, he played cricket - before he went to South Africa. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 With the St Just team?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 With Pendeen, yes. Treweallard - Trewellard, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you have books in the house as a lad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Story books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh - like - Travels of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912 Livingston}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912  and things like that. Yes, history books and - and - we weren't allowed to buy Sunday newspaper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Would any of the books have been Sunday school prizes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 All of them. Pretty well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Any newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Only the old Cornishman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was a weekly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mm. And I've got that in that book there too.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was the weekly local paper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, you weren't allowed to buy the Sunday paper when they started coming round. My schoolmaster used to have the Morning News. Yes, i
t was sent to him by post.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It wasn't sold in the area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. No. People couldn't afford it in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Any magazines available then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, they used to have things like the Sunday Companion and things. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mother would read that would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did mother or father ever read aloud to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Ever read? My mother did when - in younger days, yes. No, my father would go to the reading room, little room - very often when he came home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 There was a reading room at Pendeen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Trewellard, yes. There was an institute at Pendeen, small one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did they ever read aloud to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did mother and father ever read aloud to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. Not that I'm aware of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Do you remember a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Yes. The - the - one I remember - the - the first one I remember with any detail was my - uncle who had come home from - after spending - several years in South Africa, he went to Tasmania, and - he came home from Tasmania, and live
d about a year I should think, and he died with silicosis.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 When would that have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? About 1905 I think. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was mother's brother was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Last one of five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Was he buried in Pendeen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pendeen. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did they have walking funerals in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Yes. Nothing else. And carried - they weren't - the casket wasn't wheeled on anything, it was carried the whole distance. With bearers you know, they used to change every - and the - chapel choir used to 
sing hymns, along the - as the procession went to the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Starting at the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Yes, they sang hymns at the home first. The - the choir of the - of the - church - attended by the deceased you know. And they sang up - right up to the - graveside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Who would have attended the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Everybody in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Every - every member of the family, and - the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Children as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh yes, in those days, yes, all dressed in black. Yes. Great - usually a great
 day - a great time for the tailors in here in those days. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You would have been about nine then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
a, about nine, but I - I used to sleep with him - sometimes, because he used to get through the window and he couldn't get back and he wanted air for breathing you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 He lived in your house did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
No, he didn't, he lived with an aunt, because his wife died in Tasmanai. Mm. That's the reason he came home with one young son. Incidentally he's got cancer of the throat in London now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 The son was looked after then by granny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 By an aunt, yes. Mm. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And you went along to help your aunt with this uncle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 To be with him at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, that's right. I was sent there, put there. To call them you see in case he wanted help. You wouldn't do that nowadays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You had seen a number of people with silicosis I expect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh yes. Oh yes. All - all the miners coming home in those days from South Africa had silicosis.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It was a long lingering death wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Yes. Terribly, they couldn't walk sometimes for it. Couldn't breathe. It's the sili - silica and the syracite in the - in the reef out there you see, quartz, silica and syracite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Particularly sharp particles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon. Oh yes, yes, extremely sharp. Very fine and sharp the - dust you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Everybody who attended the funeral wore mourning clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. All the families.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did they wear such things as widows weeds, long black veils?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Not that I'm aware of, they might have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Could you tell me the year of your marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 1924.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Where was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
I told you, in Quebec - Mon - Montreal. Yes. May the nineteenth, 1924. So you see the anniversary was last Friday. And then I went back to the mining camp in - Timmins, in Northern}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9862284\charrsid13072912  Ontari}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 o.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You were working as a miner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, I was surveyor then, in the sur - survey office, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What was the year of your brother Richard's birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well I said I - as far as I know 1897, I - I'm uncertain.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And he lived to the age of fifty-three?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And Henry, when was he born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Twenty-second of August, 1909. That's the last.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 He was the youngest and you were the oldest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. He was five when I went in the army.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Your father you told me was married in South Africa, your mother went out to South Africa to him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. He sent her home when the Jameson Raid broke out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 They were married in 1895?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And she came home in 1899?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mm. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, 1896 we thought didn't we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Just before you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Who?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Your mother came home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That would have been 1896 wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And father stayed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I - I - I don't know you - only what I've seen or - or heard her say. As you know, I wasn't born. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And father stayed on working in Johannesburg was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, out on the East Rand, yes. Yes, I think it was the block near - right - near Joh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11147223\charrsid13072912 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 nnesburg I think. He was on - one or two mines out there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What was he doing, what type of mining work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh he was underground man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Underground miner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And he went back in 1902 and stayed for a short time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Six months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And again in 1910?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did he go to Johannesburg again then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 The same area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, he went to - later - he was mine captain on - the West Rand for four years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Was he amine captain then on the West Rand when he went out in 1910?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Not when he went out but shortly after. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 By 1911 perhaps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Yes, yes, I think - eleven or twelve. On Randfontein. He was on the next mine to Harty Edwards, you know R.T. Edwards. Well he was next - next mine to R.T. Edwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was on Randfontein?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Archie was on Purdies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Prior to becoming the mine captain what would have been the step up then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Shift boss. Yes. You had to qualify for a mine captain. You had to pass an examination in - at Johan}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11147223\charrsid13072912 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 esburg there. His certificate's number sixty-nine upstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 He had the certificate - that would have been the sixty-ninth person to obtain that certificate from the Government of South Africa?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, I take it so. Yes. Yes, that's right. I think I can show it to you up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You told me of the incident of the old man blinded in the mine who sold tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh there were several. Yes. I told you that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Would the accident have been due to explosions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, I think so, yes. There were quite a few of them then you know - that was - when - black powder was - used mostly I believe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did they use the safety fuse then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
I - I don't - think so, I think that was the trouble. Or if they did it wasn't - profic - protected like - you see, I don't know you see because before my time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You mentioned one or two who were blinded.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That's right. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So it was fairly general?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Usually in the blasting accidents.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 When we were talking about the houses in Pendeen I think you referred to the miners cottages as crowls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, I didn't, no. No, they used to have a lot of these old things - on the common, they were probably a hundred years old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What was the word you used?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Crow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 How do you spell that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Crow I suppose. Well that's the St Just wo
rd for them. Yes. They were made of huge rocks and clay you know. They had no - no - light - no windows or anything like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Somewhat like the Irish crofters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, well - yes, you get them around - some of the old things now, great big stones they're made of and - pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You see the walls still standing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Very seldom but around - some places you can, but they're mostly all gone. Yes. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 When you were talking about your home there and your father paying a nominal rent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And rehabilitating the whole thing, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 To Lord Falmouth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Have you any idea what a nominal rent at that time would have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Fif - fifty bob a year, but he spent a lot of money on the house you know himself. Lord Fal
mouth - had it when the life fell off, you know the lives system they used to have then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Do you remember or have you ever heard whose was the last life that made the lease fall in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Someone called Leonard Hump}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11147223\charrsid13072912 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 ries.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Someone from the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Yes. Someone that my father had worked with evidently. His was the life - the last life I understand. Yes. I didn't know him of course. Because one always had to be home with the other youngsters you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Your outings would have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Sunday school outings that's all. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 How often would that happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 About once a year. Never - I don't remember it ever}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11147223\charrsid13072912  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 happening twice. Unless you went away with the Rechabites or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 The Rechabites were attached to the chapel were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, I don't think so. Some - temperance - yes. Couldn't tell you anything about them though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you go visiting friends, relations and neighbours with your parents from time to time?
