\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 They wrapped their - religion up in the - drawer with the clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You feel some did that, didn't practice what they preached in the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well you know seemed to me, yes. Yes. Although you're not as old as I am. But - and do you know there was more dis
sention in chapels - then - then one party would break off from the other and so on, they did you know, all - that's the reason all so many chapels all put up. They all breaking away from one now - one or the other. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Do you know if your chapel at Pendeed was a Methodist or Wesleyan?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It was Wesleyan, built in 1837. 1837.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And your parents attended twice on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, my mother didn't go on Sunday mornings. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 She would be at home preparing the lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 But father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You would have gone to Sunday school in the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Absolutely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You told me that once a year there was a Sunday school outing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That's apart from the tea treat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh yes, yes, used to go to - Carbis Bay or - or Marisan or anything like that you see. From Pendeen. Four or five buses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Would they be horse}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11147223\charrsid13072912 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 drawn buses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes - oh yes, nothing else then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was one of the outings that you had to forego for going swimming was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, for - for telling a lie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Were there any other activities organized by the church or chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That you took part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What about the Band of Hope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 The Band of Hope had a very big - I think because that had all the - the denominations you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 All together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Yes, they - the Band of Hope was - was a - everybody - every - it was a great Saturday night's singing and that. That old chap there he said - oh - he said, I'm t
alking about the peers, he said, not the pears that grow on a tree but the peers of the realm you know, you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was somebody who was speaking to the Band of Hope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, an old carpenter. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What sort of form did the meetings of the Band of Hope take? Didyou attend any of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Always, yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did they have talks by different people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, by him, they - they were addressed - by this old carpenter, any one part - or anyone particular who came there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And you were exhorted to be teetotallers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Fancy I started at the place in 1903, now what did I know about -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You signed the pledge? The pledge not to drink intoxicating drinks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes, have beverages. But I have since.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was in 1903?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, now what did I know about that. I found it one day - I found it - one day, years ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You don't still have it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you belong to the choir yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Choir? No, I never - in that class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You weren't a singer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, I used to - make a noise. My - my sister was in a choir after. Later yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I suppose they would have choir outings once a year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I - I don't - know if they did or not, you see that would be before my - I I don't know whether the choir did
, I believe they did occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 But you'd no experience of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Royalties you see, and the miner was getting about fifty bob a month at that time, if we - when I started underground they were getting a pound a week. A - a day's pay miner - under - working underground all day, three and four pence a day you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 They would have been the De Dunstanville, the Bassett family were owners of mineral rights weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Just like the Boscowans, the Lord Falmouth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, that's right and the Williams's over there and all that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It probably made the underground miners rather bitter? Or determined to alter it a bit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well you see - they - they were getting a lot of money for nothing you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Just because of heredity it was felt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Yes. Yes. Of course the - the thing was, the price of tin used to - the metal, copper and tin used to fluctuate so much - in those days - you see, these smelters and that, they made pot - pots of money out to the mines you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 The smelters were situated apart from the mines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 In South Wales yes. Well, of course, the - Williams Harvey and they had - smelting works up around Redruth you know. Yes. Yes. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Would you think that was why your father held Radical views, because of the unfairness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh - my - most miners were. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did mother share those views do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? I - I think she was too busy with the family. Of course she - she hadn't got the vote then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 She would have been guided by father in any case I expect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I should think so.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Do you remember your mother or father voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh my word, yes, my father voted every time - there was an election.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And you can remember it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 There was one in 1910 actually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 1906 there was a big election you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You can remember that 1906 one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mm hm. Sir Clifford Quarry was our member down here. Yes. And he used to give his - Parliamentary sala
ry, four hundred pounds, to the - hospital up here, and they used to think that it was a wonderful thing. Now years later when I was - came home during the last war and was - an officer - official on the open cast coal - in charge of - of - portion of the
 
South Wales coalfield - I remember - dealing with the Corry interests up there because I had to go and get - sites for this open cast coal. And - there was a case a few years ago where - as a - Powell Duffryns had a - a law suit with the Cory interest, he
 - he left a million three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11147223\charrsid13072912  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
quarter pounds in - in - in one party alone, he was giving four hundred pound a year down here, they thought him wonderful you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I expect four hundred pounds a year was quite a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, but not for him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 But it was for the hospital?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mm. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 He would have been Conservative I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Liberal. Of course he was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 In some places at that time men felt they risked losing their job or their house if they voted different from their employers, d
o you know if your father felt himself under that kind of pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. Certainly not, no. No. I don't think that happened down here. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You said he was Radical, was he a member of the Radical party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, no, not a member. I don't think there were such parties then. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So there wouldn't have been any working for such things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
No. Oh he was working - in partnership with - eleven others you see I mean they had - they were their own boss. I mean they employed men do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I mean he didn't work for the Radical party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, no, no, no. But I went to a meeting once or twice with him and I know there was all those quarrels.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Your father would go to a political meeting prior to the election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh yes. Oh yes, he great - he was a great Liberal, great Radical. He was always called that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What would happen at the meeting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 All arguments you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Speeches and arguments?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 One was free trade and the other was protection of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I suppose the Radicals were free trade were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
I was - many years old before I - before I actually had a vote because I was never home you see - later on. You see, when I grew up I was trave}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11147223\charrsid13072912 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 ling all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 When your parents weren't at work did they have outside interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Not that I'm aware of. Oh - my father was always - interested in cricket, but he didn't play, not after he married I don't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did mother involve herself in any outside interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. No. No. She had too much to do at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I suppose as in most cases the chapel would be the main social event?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. She didn't go often because she had so many children. She did later.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 After the children grew up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 When father was working at home what time would his work finish in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Oh I think he used - about - four or half past four. See, what they used be doing was filling - dirt into carts to send down to the mill you see, for crushing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 He would spend his evenings at home after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? Oh he'd go to the read - some local reading room. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Leaving off at half past four did that mean that he started very early in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, I think he left home about seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Father did attend this reading club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And he was a teetotaller?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So he wouldn't have attended any pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. He was a non-smoker too. And I never heard - heard him use foul language.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 The small institute at Pendeen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 The small institute at Pendeen where he used to read the papers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, he used to go to a small room in Trewellard. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Was that called an institute?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, it was - yes, a reading room, upstairs in a - cottage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Can you tell me anything about that, how was it founded, who owned it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh no, just - a bunch of the - local men you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Working man's institute?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
It wasn't a working man's club, no, this was a reading room. They had a working man's club at St Just, they had an institute at Pendeed, but this was 
a reading room at Rewellard where he used to go. Yes. It was in the - it was in the - cottage belonging to the chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Attached to the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Empty cottage, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Who would organize it and see about the papers for the reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh I - they - would amongst themselves - you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 They'd have a number of daily papers to read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
I believe one or two, that's all. One I believe. You see they had darts and - a - a draught board and things like that there too, a discussion room you see, between themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It was really a modest type of club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, small - small - small membership.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Was it exclusive to men or did your mother go too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, no. No, no. Never had any - women in those days never had any - you know, call on anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11147223\charrsid13072912 Their interests wer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 e in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, that's right. That was generally acknowledged then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did father take any part in sport apart from his cricket?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Would there have been any races anywhere near?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh
 yes, there were always races on Feast - Feast Monday, St Just Feast Monday, there were always races. Foot race with men and a horse race. And there was also horse racing at - St Buryan. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Who would take part in those horse races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh local - local farmers and that as far as I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Father would go to those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 On St Just Feast Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What time of year would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? Oh - the - the St Just Feast - yes, but they would have - competitions in February a
nd drilling and - ploughing and hedging. That was held in the - in - in - February I think every year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Who would organize that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well I suppose a local committee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Sort of farming committee?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, not farmers necessarily. Some local committee I think. As far as I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was held in February at the ploughing time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Plain-an-Gwarry up at St Just.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 There's a Plain-an-Gwarry at Redruth too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Do you know what that name meant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, that's old Cornish -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did father or mother belong to any savings clubs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, there were no savings clubs in those days, more than Bar - Bolitho's Bank in here. No. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was just straightforward banking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 In some areas they had Provident Funds for sickness and burial and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Oh that was in the mines - the mine - miners paid about I think a sixpence or a shilling every time a miner died - they - there was a - there was a - mine - some kind of small club in - in - in each mine as far as I understand
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That would be paid after the tragedy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, I think it was kept out - once a month, sixpence or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 They paid into it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. And if a miner died I believe there was sixpence extra deducted or something like that. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What about hospital savings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
I don't know. Not aware of any. I believe the hospital up here was voluntary then as far as I know. They had - certain - kind of subscription day or flag days if you like to call them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And then the four hundred from the member of Parliament?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? Yes. Yes. -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Your own leisure before you left school, as a child who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh I don't - oh half of the boys in the village. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? No. Not usually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 They were too young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters, did you fight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh got - yes, normally. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You had your squabbles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, I don't think we had anything particular
 like that. No, I don't remember ever - quarrelling with my - not - scrapping or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 When I was a child I was closer to my brother who was nearer my age than the others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Uh huh. Well my sister was four years younger than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So that's quite a bit of difference as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. You - she wrote me very often when I was in the army. And she would be about fourteen when I went away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 As a child you were closer to her than the others? Due to the age would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I don't know, all the same I think. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 When you went out to play did you play in the garden or other peoples homes or in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, there were common - anywhere where there was a small patch where you could play marbles or anything. No
where particular, down in the moors jumping pools and that. You see? Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And you would play marbles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 The same as everybody else, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 On the road outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 We got held up if we did, when you went home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You had to watch it a bit?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 My mother's influence was very strong in those days. Especially with your father away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, of course. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did your parents discourage you from playing with any other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, no, no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No cares about it at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, they had their own opinion of other peoples children but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You weren't stopped from playing with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you belong to any youth organizations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? No, there were none.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No Boy Scouts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Nor the Boys Brigade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, when I came home from the army - the old minister got me to be the - take charge of the St Just Boys Brigade, that
's when old C.B. Thomas - for one - Feast Monday - he was preaching at St Just and I had the Boys Brigade there, and he promised them what - any help they wanted, and when - when the minister wrote to him - he - he didn't - turn up so he told me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 He let them down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 But there was no Boys Brigade while you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 When you were at school did you have any hobbies?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, I used to - no, not - go out - from the first I always - collected minerals. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was a hobby which led to a profession?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What would you do with them, keep them in a case?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 All over the place they were. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Were you interested - you collected minerals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you collect anything else, were you interested in shells?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Not necessarily, no. Stones and minerals, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you keep any pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? No, no. We had enough pets there. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you yourself do any gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I - only what I had to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Which would be weeding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Potatoes and - putting in potatoes and that - in the back garden - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And digging them I suppose when the time came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, that's right, digging 'em when the time came.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Were you interested in fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 The miners - my father and
 his partners and all them, they used to have - more or - a bit of competition, I've heard - I always remember them measuring the - onion one day and they said well that one's fourteen inches I always remember that. They had potato - they had onions as mu
ch as fourteen inches in cir - circumference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did they have competitions for vegetables?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No competitions, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No exhibitions like they have now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, just ordinary -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Amongst themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Were you interested in fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, there was a fish rock right underneath - the cliff - where all miners used to go. Down underneath a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11147223\charrsid13072912 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912  three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11147223\charrsid13072912  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
hundred foot cliff there between Botallack and - and - Levant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 With rod and line?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? With line yes. They used pilchard for bait. It was - they had - access by - ladders down the cliff face and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Rather dangerous?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Very. Yes. Very. But that was one of the - recreations of the miners you know, was fishing in season, summertime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 A good fresh air occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 On rock, yes. Very dangerous down there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 The big waves could come up sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes, very dangerous down there sometimes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you go for long walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. If - if we felt like it we went to Ken - Kenidjack with
 a - big - big bunch of rocks is - do you know that big bunch of rocks on the - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11147223\charrsid13072912 S}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
t Just Road going up - mm - I - I - actually I - I proposed to my wife up there one Sunday night, a long way, right up in the common you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That's got a special interest for you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? Oh very much so, yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And as a boy that was where you went walking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you cycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? I didn't have a bicycle until I were working in the mines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So that didn't happen while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, never had any money for bicycles then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you take part yourself while at school in any sports
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You played cricket at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh yes, cricket on the moor here, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Were you able to go to any theatres?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Where would they be held then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Coo, I don't know, well - of course a bit rare, sometimes at school, the day school had a concert perhaps once in - two or three year. There wasn't much entertainment in that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 These concerts would be given by the children themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Mm. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, none. None.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Plymouth would be the nearest wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? Oh I never - I - when I went in the Army I'd never been beyond Truro.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No cinemas while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? No, no, no, no. No. NO.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Your parents gave you pocket money of a penny a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well not more than that. I generally had four}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11147223\charrsid13072912  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 pence at feast time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Or if there was something special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mm. Very seldom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Can you remember what you spent it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. I know it didn't last very long. Some of it went - or if - when I had four}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11147223\charrsid13072912  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 pence all went in chip by chip in - ha'porth or a pennorth. I was generally coming home when ever
ybody else was going. You know, in those days - Whit Monday and Feast and that was when the couples used to pair of you know. Yes. Yes. St Swithins Day everybody round Pendeen used to - assemble down a place called the Boat Cove, north of the - Pendeen li
ght house. They used to go there from as far as two or three miles away you know. They'd been - they've been reviving it lately.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was a social focal point?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes, that was on - St Swithin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11147223\charrsid13072912 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 s Day I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That's in September isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, it's in the summer, in - in the - if it rained in - on St Swithin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11147223\charrsid13072912 
\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 s Day it rains forty days they say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It's high summer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after her house or family
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Not that I'm aware of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That's your own responsibility.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 If mother was ill or confined to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh it was very seldom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Do you remember what happened when the younger children were born, someone would come in to help then would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Yes, that's right, yes, always. They were born in the home. I visited a woman - when we went round the world in 1960, I visited a woman in Melbourne - who - assisted my mother - twice. I met her out in Melbourne. Not a -
 midwife, no. Yes. Used to assist. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Simply for confinements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You did have relatives living nearby didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh yes, plenty, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you see much of them when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh yes. Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did they visit much when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh normally you know, they did - sometimes - come in and - courtesy as they call it don't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Come for a bit of chat from time to time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And advice perhaps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Relations used to visit one and the other sometimes. Go as much as a mile or two miles you see and visit one and the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Apart from relations did your parents as a family have family friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh yes. Yes, they had family friends. But they had no time to go and see
 visit them when they were - they have a chat over the garden wall on a summer evening or anything like that you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did mother and father share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? Normally, yes, I think so. They were all family relatives and that you s
ee. 'Course most of our people who - who went to Australia and - Kimberley and South Africa and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did mother have any special friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Not that I'm aware of, no. More than relations.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Would the same be for father, would he have any special friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Oh he had many - many friends yes, they'd meet them you see, they - they knocked around more than - the mother whose confined to the house more than - mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 He would meet them at the club I expect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well you see, in
 the summer they would - your - you're bound to meet people in summer going to cricket match and going here, there - moving around generally, village life was - village life all the same you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It was a very much involved community?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, it was, yes. Going to Penzance was a big day, for - who - doesn't matter who it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 How often would that happen, would father visit Penzance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 He had business there I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Or cricket?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Were friends invited to the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Were friends invited to the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well they all came without invitations. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Casually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Would they stay to tea sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? Oh yes - not often because - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Were there any particular days or special occasions when friends would come?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
No I don't think so. Usually my mother used to bake bread on Saturdays. And - she used to - there used to be a wash tub put on the kitchen table and the kids used to be washed - had a bath every Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 The bathing would be done in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, on the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Always on Saturdays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That would be the big aluminium bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Had their clean clothes on Sat - Sunday. Washday was Monday. Washday was always Monday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Always the same routine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Sometimes - my mother had a little help. Used to pay a woman a shilling a day then you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That would be washdays would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Then my - my wife's - mother always had someone washing for her. The were a little better fixed than -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That would be a neighbour I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Would friends call in casually from time to time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, especially in a miners home. Yes. Well you knew miners, they - as I said, they used to 
come home at - for Whitsun or - Midsummer Day or St Just Feast they all came home from abroad then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And they would call around while they were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well - if you didn't meet them outside, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Old friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 The same would happen about neighbours I suppose, they would call just if they had some special reason?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Well yes, my - they used to - father used to meet 'em very often after - after the - service Sunday mornings in the summer, they'd go for a walk - a walk along a road you see, come back late for lunch and have hell up you see, quietly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mother would feel that the lunch was kept waiting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, that's right. Family life was the same all over then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It was pretty well tied to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It was pretty well tied to the church and your employment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And the house. Yes. Oh my father wasn't a church leader or anything. Pretty staunch -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Supporter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 People often tell us that in those days they made their own amuseme
nts, what do you think your parents did when they got together with their friends and neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? That's right, that's true.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Can you think of any entertainments that your parents organized together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Simply chatting and talking about mutual interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I suppose so, I - as a rule the kids were pushed out the way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Any music played when they had visitors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Any? Oh we had a - a - in - a - when I was a boy - the piano was a great thing in St Just and who h
ad the best piano - and I - I had - music lessons from the time I was twelve 'til I was fourteen, used to go a mile.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It was a bit of a status symbol was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? I suppose so but I didn't know enough about it at that time, I used to - hate practicing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 If they had friends in would they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh maybe play the piano. Yes. And - and this I used to hate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did your brothers and sisters hate it just as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 They had - all had music lessons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 But did they like it better than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Not that I'm aware of. I've got a brother living now who's generally playing the piano over there on Sundays. People got rid of their pianos you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 There's not much of it done now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, no, no. It's too much - music now on records and - this, that and the other things. Radio.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort different from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. I were always brought up that - children shouldn't - talk when the elders are talking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Were you ever told to curtsey or touch your cap to anyone?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Many people divide society into different social classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Not in mining villages. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Was there anyone that you thought of as in a different class in that locality.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well of course children don't think of class you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And they weren't taught to think of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
No. Oh no. No. My father was always - of the opinion that if a - a young miner had studied and got on that he was a man to be respected. Always did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That wouldn't have put him into another class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. No. But the fact that he had - got on - put him a bit above another person. But - but he had to get on by his own efforts you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That would be the people who had ambition?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And worked for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. I - I suppose I would come in that myself. Although as I - might have been - a miner all my life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 In the Pendeen and in the district generally who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I don't - I don't know. The - the - mining engineer who was trave}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11147223\charrsid13072912 l}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
ling a lot - for examining mine, and old - cousin of my mother's called Captain Andrew, he used to go all over the world, be sent all over the world, he would be - oh Captain Andrew - or Captain so and so, any mine Captain the
y used to - yes. Yes. And everybody - who's - a boss in the mine was always Captain so and so you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 He was held in esteem by the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 More or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you come into contact with mine captains yourself as a lad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 When I started work.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 But not as a schoolchild?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. I - I got fired once or twice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 They were considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well - I don't know about that but they were - a little apart from the others you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What about shopkeepers, who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, the bank. They -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Was there a bank in your village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, Penzance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What about the clergy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh I never took any notice of clergy. No. The minister was always the - looked upon I suppose as a little - different from other people.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That would be the Methodist minister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, or - or the parson, but - I think -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Who would the minister would think was his special -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? Oh I don't know. I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You've mentioned that you called your headmaster sir,?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Only a - rarest occasions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 At school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Who do you think he would have associated with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I used to spend -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You mentioned the headmaster, you called him sire, who would have been his social - he would have considered his -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
He - he used to mix with - my father and - and my wife's father and all that - that type of man. He - I mean there were certain type who'd stand up in the village and - and go into the pub or - or - when - when the chapel's on a bunch of m
iners would always congregate not far away, and in the summer time there used to be twenty and thirty miners sometimes in a bunch. The mine - the - the headmaster used - was a friend of my father's, but he was a great patriot, he - he was always telling u
s instilling into us boys all about - Britain - being - our heritage if you like, that's one of the things that made me join the army so quickly. Being a citizen of Britain. Used to be proud of it in those days. They aren't now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Who?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Farmers, were they of any special social importance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
No. No, no. No, I think farmers had pretty hard time in those days you know. Yes, farmers had to work then, everything was hand - manual work in those days you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And they would be too busy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
No, farmers used to often drive their cart - horse and cart - to haul - rock for my father and then down to the mill. Down - down to the - sort of water stamps down to Kenidjack, they'd get six shillings a day for six cart loads of stuff, their ho
rse and cart and themselves, and they'd pull six loads, about a mile for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 They would combine that with their farming?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes. Yes. It was a little side line more or less you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Sort of hire their horses and carts out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. And you - they'd get a ticket for six loads. Then they had those in they had their pay at the end of the month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 They were fairly small farms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Generally around there, yes, yes. Forty acres and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And of poor quality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well I - it was a - a pretty - hard existence really you know, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Would there be any other employers in Pendeen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, I don't know - there were a couple of local carpenters and so on, and there was a blacksmith. He'd mend the hoop you had for a can
dle, you know, if you broke your hoop he'd mend it for a candle you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Sort of barter instead of passing money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What sort of people would you say went to church as opposed to chapel? Any difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well they used to think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 They thought they were a superior social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 U - usually, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Can think of anyone who would have come into that category?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. They were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 The same sort of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, yes, that's right, yes, but - in election - at election time there were always - Conservative - Unionists you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 The church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 The Establishment voted Conservative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And the chapel people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Generally Liberal. Yes. Nine times out of ten in those times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or would you say that there were different groups?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh I would say that - we probably lived as well - if not better than anybody in the village, I sh
ould think so. I think - I think our standard of living was - yes, I should think so.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You could have been described as upper working class really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mm - well, very much working class all the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 But rather better off than some?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
 Yes, my father - was earning somewhere around three pounds a week when the others - were earning one. I know that much, because I found - I found the figures since then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Would one group have felt themselves superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. Only - yes,
 I mean you knew your standard of decency and - if your father didn't go to pub and drink and - and your sis - your brothers and sisters were always dressed clean and - nice and whole - I mean nothing shoddy, when they were going to church or - or chapel 
on Sundays they were always beautifully clean and always - I've heard remarks passed - about them. Now my parents were very industrious, both of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Self respecting people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Were there families who were thought of as rough and others respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 There were plenty of them, yes. Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was a sort of distinction?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh yes. Yes, there was a kind of a - a social standing - although they didn't think anything more of you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It was your own self respect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Do you remember a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh generally, yes, well I mean - a craftsman always had extra pay you know
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 A slight distinction?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes. Oh craftsman's always - superior to a labourer.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And the craftsmen in Pendeen would have been carpenters and the shoemaker would have come into that wouldn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, not normally, they were generally considered to be impoverished you know
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 But still they were craftsmen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh y
es, yes, and - and skilled craftsmen too. I had a pair of boots made by our local shoemaker and I - and I wore - wore them - for - until I was commissioned? - I wore them right up through Mes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11147223\charrsid13072912 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 potamia and all that. Beautiful pair of boots for a pound you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you have your shoes made as children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 A - a local shoemaker, yes. Not your best shoes of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 They were bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, but - the ordinary - work - working shoes and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Your school shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did father and mother both have the same attitude to people in different classes and groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 As far as I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 They themselves belonged to the same social group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Oh yes, very much so. Old mining family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Would this be because they came from the same walk of life and the same locality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I suppose so. I suppose so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Was it possible at that time to move from one class or group to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I don't think there was any desire for that. If you - if you - did it became - cam
e gradually, according to - one's social - one's - I suppose financial status.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I suppose it's possible to move down as well as up, would some folk have moved down a bit?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh I think those - who were low couldn't fall any lower.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 But the only way was up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, you can be poor but you can be honest you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Do you remember anyone specially being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. No, but there were such people. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Who would they be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh I don't know, they - they would be - I mean some very respected old mining men who came home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was because they were people who were highly respected?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Like - one of my father's partners who was a - a - a great-uncle to my wife and - he cross the
 Panama before the canal was there, he crossed it on mule}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11147223\charrsid13072912 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 back to - take a job as a mine captain down in - in E}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11147223\charrsid13072912 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
uador, and he was out in Kimberley with Cecil Rhodes, and he's out on the West coast of New Zealand washing sand for gold. Took ninety - pardon me, ninety-three days to come home. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 He was distinguished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
He was a very fine old gentleman, yes. And he told me when I was going to travel - as long as you were square with everybody if you left a mining camp you were all right, but if they said you're crooked, you - you couldn't say anything worse about you.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That would follow you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 When you were a child -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well I'm growing up all the time you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You said in one place that you would run to granny if you saw a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 If I was at my granny's and saw a policeman I would stay there, I wouldn't go in.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you see the policeman around very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well he used to talk to my father when - when he was feeding the chickens and - he was keen on chicken himself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Sort of a social chit-chat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Oh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11147223\charrsid13072912  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
yes, yes, very much so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did he get around on foot or on a bicycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Generally on foot - at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did he live in the locality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. About a half a mile away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did your mother ever say to you if you were misbehaving, I'll call a police man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Of course, yes. Yes. She didn't have to call him, I was scared of him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Had you any reason for being scared of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Only boy - boyhood pranks, that's all. Setting fire to furze bushes near ripe cornfields and so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Which you knew you shouldn't do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Sort}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11147223\charrsid13072912  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
of a guilty conscience?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, I had a - a - guilty conscience yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 How do you think the policeman treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh, all right. Yes. Yes. All right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Friendly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 A policeman in those days, he kept a - yes, they had more respect for a policeman then than they have now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did he ever give you a talking to, and tell you to not do things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh if - if anybody grown up telling you - doing mischief they used to - to of course - tell you, I mean that's normal, natural.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You mention that your home was rented, you paid a nominal rent, did you ever see anything of the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, they had - a - a rent day at a hotel in St Just, once a year I think. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So everybody went to that room on that day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes. Went there and paid their rental to - Lord - Lord Falmouth's steward. Steward of Lord Falmouth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What did you feel about him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Lord Falmouth? It - it - didn't see him at all, it was his - it was his steward that they had to deal with, and they weren't over nice. They were very nasty sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Were they condescending?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, in a way of speaking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 How was he as a landlord, did he keep the property in repair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, my father had to keep his own property, I told you he had an agreement to this - extent. Nominal rental. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Do you remember ever feeling that your parents had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. No. No, I never felt - found that atmosphere in my home ever. I was always proud of my father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did any families have to apply to the Guardians in the parish for charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No - some families used to come to my - mother for clothing. Discards from us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 She used to pass it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 But you never heard of the Guardians?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 In some areas they were quite prominent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, but not - since the turn of the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11147223\charrsid13072912 cent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 ury really, no. People used to still go to the work house in those days you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Which would be where?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Up here, Madron.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That's if they were completely homeless?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Great stone steps up there I understand, cold. Yes. Things were bad you know in Corn - everywhere in the old days you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 If you fell on hard times they were very hared?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh very hard, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Do you remember if there was someone in the district whom the people disapproved of strongly was there any special way in which they showed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. You had - had
 nothing to do with them I suppose. No, I - I mean if a man wanted to get drunk he got drunk and - that's all - it was his own money. He could get - beer for tuppence a pint and all that sort of thing and what man did nothing to do with the other man. Lon
g as he didn't steal and this, that and the other thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 There was nobody who did that sort of thing against his neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, not normally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Any meanness, no meanness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What they did wrong was to themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Were you given lessons by either of your parents or a tutor?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.- No I had to study myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh about five. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 When you first started what time of the morning did you go and what time did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well the school was just across the green, only about a hundred yards from the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That would be from nine 'til half past three would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Nine until twelve and then from - two I think until half past four. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And you went all day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What kind of school was it? Was it a Board school or a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mixed - mixed - mixed - county school, coun - council, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mixed for infants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And - and the same for - when you passed out of the infants school it was still - a mixed school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Would that be a Board school or a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, it was - a Cornwall County Council School. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Boys and girls mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And it was just across the road from where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So in two or three minutes you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. I - normally I was - the - always in the top two in the class when it came on the - on the board.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did anybody take you to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you come home to lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Like everybody, not much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Not much as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well I was glad when I was fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So you didn't like it all that much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 We didn't real - we didn't - appreciate things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well, all - all schoolchildren have nickname for their teacher, or had in those days. I've heard ours called everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Was it from malice or was he liked or disliked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well - I've never known - a schoolmaster to be liked yet, not in my time. He was a good fellow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You mentioned that he was the only one that took the local paper, the Western Morning News?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Which was sent to him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That's true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did he read it to you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You just noticed that he had the paper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, patriotism.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11147223\charrsid13072912  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
about manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh I don't know. Your - your parents told you when a thing's bad manners or - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You didn't need the teaching in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, parental control was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Most children were well mannered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well, in our house I believe they were. Especially at table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did the teachers teach tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? No. I don't think so. Some - children used to come to school in a awful state. You can always tell the home from they came from.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Some would come from quite poor homes I expect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. I don't mean poor but you could be clean you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Would any of them ever come without shoes on their feet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. No, never. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 They did in some parts of the country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Not down there, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What about punctuality, did they teach you to be punctual?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well you had to be, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What happened if you weren't then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well - if you came late I - I don't know, but it's normally most - children were always punctual.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did they correct ways of speaking or teach you ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 A smack in the ear. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That's the way they'd punish you? Girls the same as boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Would they treat girls the same as boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh I didn't - I never seen girls - no. Cane - no, I've had canes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 A cane on the hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Pull the hand back you know. And get two instead of one. Not often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You said jokingly a smack behind the ear, would they do that often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. Very seldom. Very seldom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And not very heavily?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. No. No. No I didn't see a lot of capital punishment, no. But the cane, the old cane came round sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What would they give you the cane for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh - I mean, if you're - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11147223\charrsid13072912 m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 isbehaving you would have cane of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Talking in class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, like that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I - I suppose, yes, normally, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did they ask you what you'd done at school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Normally they'd find out - they'd know, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did they ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Or meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? Oh yes, they used to meet the teachers - in - normally, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Where would they meet them then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well - meet them on the - on the road or in the village or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And have a chat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, yes, or at the end - any game there was on or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did the teachers live in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Always, they were local.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That's the difference today isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mm. Everyone knew everyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You have said that some children came from more untidy and poorer homes than your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was evidenced by their own clothing and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Children would often - ask to - be allowed to go early to take - a hot lunch to t
heir - father when they - had the ore sent up from underground and used to be cleaning it on the floors, tributers what they call, they used to go - they used to say please can I go early cardinner, which meant - please can I go early to carry - lunch to 
my father. That used to happen - a certain period every month if their father was - working on tribute, in - in the mine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Could you tell me what tributers means?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well, a tributer gets so much for the tin that he raises. Brings up to the surface, 
and when he's brought up to the surface he - he's paid two or three - three or four days cleaning it, before it is - taken for sampling and weighing and all that sort of thing. Then on the value of the tin in the ore so he gets paid - so much in the pound
. It's too long a thing to - it's too long a process to - to describe in a - in a short time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I was wondering why the children would carry dinners especially when their fathers were working on tribute.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well I said when he's on surface cleaning the - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
No, I don't think so. Some children were naturally stupid you know, I - I knew four of five of 'em who were - wouldn't have any - and yet one or two of 
'em - is late - were late starters, now there's a fellow called William Nicholls, Nicholas, he - he - he's a County council}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
or and all the rest of it but he was the biggest - thickhead I ever seen in my life. His father was a manager at Levant one time, I 
think he has a chemists shop in Redruth Nicholls - I think he - had one down in Megavissy. I think he's chairman of the police committee in Cornwall and all that now. He's - but he was the biggest thickhead I ever met in my life. His father - the - manage
r of Levant was always very - very decent to me, especially when I came out of the Army. I had many a chat with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 But the boy was slow at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? No, no, no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Were any children left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. Nothing to be left out of you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Not in the games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. There were not games at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What happened in the playtime then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well you went out in a - went out in the yard and kicked up a fuss.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Played with tops and marbles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well - made a noise generally, there wasn't much you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Worked off their spirits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you go on to another school after this board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. I changed from Carnyorth to Pendeen, that was all, I went out there but that wouldn't make any difference. The - the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Why did you change from Carnyorth to Pendeen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Because I had my chums were - went out - were out there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You wanted to go because of friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, I was very silly. That had nothing to do with my - schooling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Why do you say you were silly then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Pardon? Well because I had to walk very much farther than I - need have done. But I liked the - I wouldn't go back again when the new master came there because I - I liked the - my - my friends at - where I was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 At Pendeen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pendeen, yes. I used to go out again at night, in night school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Fourteen. Yes. But I - I continued on - night classes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Would you have stayed longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I don't think I wanted to, I wanted to - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 The curricu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 lum wouldn't have taught you anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 They never - the curriculum did - didn't include grammar and that's one of the things I missed all my life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Evening classes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. I - I went from Monday until Saturday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 After you left work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You went to evening classes from Monday to Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I came home and I studied until about se
ven and I went to evening classes. Then I came back after nine and studied 'til midnight very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 These evening classes, where did you go for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pendeen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pendeen school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pendeen day school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Algebra and - Euclid - English, geometry. Lit - English literature. Mostly, then Saturdays - assaying and chemistry. Minerology.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Is this also at Pendeen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. That's at Botallack on Saturdays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Was that at the school as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Branch at the - a branch of the Camborne school of Mines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What premises at Botallack?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? Oh there was a small - there's a long bungalow down there that was built for that purpose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 For evening classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 By the Cornwall Education Committee?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, and surveying course in summertime. From Camborne School of Mines used to come down there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It was a branch of the Camborne School of Mines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well - yes. It were run under the - staff of the - Cornwall County Council from the Camborne School of Mines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 There you studied surveying did you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Mathematics, mineralogy, chemistry, assaying. From four 'til nine. And you saw the certificates I had the other day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You gained some qualifications there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You gained certificates at Botallack in what subjects?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
As - Assaying - mineralogy - chemistry - and - in 1914 I had a certificate in the survey, after two months of the survey class. And then I ran away and joined the Army.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 If you hadn't run away and joined the Army could you have gone on to some further education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
I could have gone to Camborne School of Mines but my mother said she couldn't afford it. I didn't want - I had no desire to, the war had broken out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Had you gained an entry to the Camborne School of Mines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes I had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Was that by a competitive examination?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well it was for my work in the night classes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You were awarded it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, I was awarded that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 By?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Cornwall County Council.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That would be the Cornwall Education Committee?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That sounds to me as if it was a special award, did many people gain those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. I was the first one I believe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 First one from Pendeen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Look - that's running out you know, you'd better watch it now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You must have worked hard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I did, yes. Yes, I - I meant to get out of - the - being a miner. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was after you left school you did the metal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 urgy classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Do you have any regrets apart from the lack of grammar about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, I don't think so, more than - there were no such thing as - as - as - wh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 t do you call it, the speech - what do you call it now, what's the word I want to use? Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You said there were no such things as elocution lessons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, and grammar wasn't taught you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Thos are two subjects you would have liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Very much. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Do you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? What school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Any of the schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I must have done. I must - oh - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 While you were at school did you do any part time work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. All study, I had to - study all the time, but even when I was - about thirteen, I was - it's on the red look. Well I can see the red.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Where did you go for the examinations on these mining subjects?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 At the Pendeen evening school on mining subjects, but the - assaying and that at the Penzance School of Mines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You had no part time jobs when you were at school because of the evening classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh no, I never - we never had any part time job in those days. Children didn't have part time job then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I should like to ask you about your first full time job after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh I went in Levant. Underground at Levant mine. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 How did you get that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 How did I get it? Just asked for it, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You yourself went along?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Boys always went underground then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It wouldn't have been done through your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 My father was in Africa.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So you'd have gone along on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, of course, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What exactly did you have to do in this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Ay? Oh I had - had to help - help the miners and drill - drill the hole, bore the hole, I had to bore with a hammer and a drill the same as they did. And carry the - carry the canteen of water and - get the explosives and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Generally tend the miners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You would generally tend the experienced miners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, and - and do the same work as they did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well I went to - I left my home at half past six and I got home about quarter past, half past four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you work on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What about Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. All week except full pay on - pay Saturday sometime. Miners didn'
t work - they - they didn't have any paid holidays in those days, any holiday you took you didn't get paid for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No holidays with pay and no half days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. No, you couldn't go all that way down, it used to take you about an hour, an hour and a half to get down there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 To get down to the underground place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Where you worked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Take you half an hour on the main engine alone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was where you went underground?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What would the pay have been to start with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Me? One and three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 pence a day. Seven and six a week, yes, thirty bob a month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was general at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes - well I don't know about general - yes, I - I suppose underground as a rule. That was thirty bob a month if you had - if 
your miners had two - two days off during the month you had your two days off as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you give any of the money to your mother?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Gave it all to my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was general too wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 How did you get on with the other people at the mine that you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Well I didn't get on with one of them, and I - but I got on with the other, he had the DCM in France after. I didn't get on with one of 'em, a very teasing man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Poor tempered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Very - a very poor tempered man. I used to see him after I'd been trave}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 ling a lot, he used to carry post at St Just. He was a good miner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 But no patience?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Who would you reckon to be your employer, the mine owner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, Levant mine. Levant Mining Company.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Would you see anything of the employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well if - the - Levant Mining was a company the same as you had a manager you had a mine captain.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Who would be directly responsible for you or your boss?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well the men that I worked with would be responsible for me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And you got on well with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 With one of 'em, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 How did you feel about the work itself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Hated it. Yes. I wanted to travel, that's the reason I went underground.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It would have been heavy work underground wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Ay? Very. Very. Very, with a candle you know, the only illumination was a candle. The temperature was about a hundred, saturated air, terrible.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Very hot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It was - you - worked with a pair of boots and a - linen pant
s on, nothing more. And your boots used to turn up like that, for the - poor the perspiration out. No stockings of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And I suppose the deeper you got the hotter it would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, sometimes some places were better ventilated than others. Yes
. No, some pretty hot places there. It was very hot and - humid place where I started to work. I couldn't have been in a worse place I don't think - in Levant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And that was at the age of fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Fourteen. Mm. I shifted around a lot in the mine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Would that have been doing different types of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, and in different places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Different levels I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. If the prices weren't good enough you quit, and then they give you somewhere - somewhere else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Depending on the amount of tin you could find?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, depending on the amount of ground you could break - rock you could break Tut work that's called. Two system, tut work and tribute.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Tut work would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So much a fathom. And tribute was so much for the metal you - raised. So much percentage of the value.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 How long did you stay underground after that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Oh I - I went to Geevor for five months and I went back to Levant, I was underground - four years and - four months, altogether. Four years and - four - four years - April, May, June, yes, July, Four - four years and four months altogether.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 After these hours of underground work you then went on to do your evening classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. I studied before I went to evening class, after I had my dinn
er, we'd call it, and - I studied when I came back. I went a mile each way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You went to Pendeen then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. And oil - old oil lamp used to blow, this chimney - smoke had to fly up through in the wintertime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That's when you were studying with the lamplight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That's - yes, and - and out at the night school. They - they didn't blow up like that in my house of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 any}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
 other lads take this course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Two or three, that's all. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Who would it have been, the local schoolmaster taking it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Not the mining lessons, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I mean the English and other subjects?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh English literature and algebra and that, the local schoolmaster. But the mining lectures were taken by a - a retired mining engineer.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And they came out from Penzance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, they didn't, they were local.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And then at eighteen you joined the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Eighteen - eighteen and a half, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And went right through the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Right through. August 1914, August 1919. We left England on the 
eleventh of December. 1914. And got back - I got back on the sixteenth of August, 1919.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You didn't come home in that time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You went to France first did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. Went to North West Frontier in India. Yes. And then - I was promoted
 Lance Corporal, later I went to Mesopotamia. And there I - was commissioned at Coat. And three months later I was sent back to India.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You went through the rest of the war in India did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, when I came back from Mesopotamia, I paid a man - three hundred rupees to - to - transfer into his - in his place to go to S}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 lonica, and then Bulgaria signed the armistice so we didn't go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So your rupees went for nothing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, my - I lost three hundred rupees.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What jobs have you done since the first war, starting from 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh I went three years to Camborne School of Mines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And this was to take up this place that you had won?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Before the war started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes. That's right. As a scholarship there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Would that have been a maintenance grant that would have helped to keep you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Yes, I think I had fifty-two pounds a year, if I - if I remember rightly. Yes, but I had to - I had been careful and I'd saved a - I had about seven hundred pounds when I - had my
 gratuities and that. I had sixteen pounds for my two and a half years in the ranks. We went through hell.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It doesn't sound very much these days does it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Then after your three years at the School of Mines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. I - went to Canada.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You qualified then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, a first class diploma. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 In surveying?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Assaying?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
No. Mining engineer. In - that - that - covers - assaying - assay - I wouldn't be an assayer not for - surveying - assay surveying, mechanic
al, electrical - geology, yes. Minerology. Chemistry. I was qualified mining engineer, as far as technical business was concerned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And a first class diploma from Camborne School of Mines was recognised all over the world was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It was, yes. Yes. Later on they awarded a - an Associateship and I was - had a first class Associateship.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And then your first appointment after gaining this qualification?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I went to Canada. In - in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 1922 or three?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mm. '22 - in the Ollinger Gold - Ol
linger Consolidated Coal mines. Timmons. Timmons Ontario. And then I went into a gold rush in Quebec, with a dog sleigh. And later my wife - I got married and my wife came up from Toronto and she went in on a horse sleigh. In Quebec. Yes. To a place calle
d Noranda - Ruan, which is now - a big city.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you stay there then at this place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Year. I was in Canada three years. Then I came home, we came home, both of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You'd been married a year then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 A year - a year and a half yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And then you came home to England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. And lived out here.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 What was the next job then after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Down - round the Spanish Main, Venezuela. Venezuela.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was mining again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 South of \{BLANK\} coalmine, very rich coalfield. That's 
where Drake and Raleigh used to go. It'll take a week to write down what I was doing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was still as mining engineer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, of course, yes. Yes, that was for a French company and they were - it - it was no good, they had no money or anything. 
They were on a shoestring. I came home in about - seven or eight months. Seven months I think. Mm. And then I went out to - Rhodesia, North West Rhodesia.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 To the copper mines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 There were no copper mines there then, I was one of the first men out
 there. There was a missionary there when I got there. And we opened - I opened the first shafts out there on the Rhone \{BLANK\} copper mine that is now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That's a very big mining place now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, very big, but there was a missionary there when I got out there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So you really helped to plan and sink those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, I didn't - I - I - I did what I was told. I h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 d to sink the shaft, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you belong to any professional organization?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, I was - I was at that time - a - a student of the Institution of Mining Metal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 urgy in 1929, I became - it - I became an Associate. 1950 I became a member.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Associate and then member?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Institution of Mining Meta}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 lurgy. IMM.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Would that involve any activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You had to - to become 
a member you had to have five years of - responsible a highly responsible job, or administration. Besides having your technical qualification. You had - you had to be elected as I remember.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Working in Rhodesia, I suppose most of the actual workers there would have been natives of the country?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh yes, we - we had them all - some miners sent from }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 Johannesburg}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 . White miners, yes, the others would be all - native. It was always growing - always growing, expanding as - whilst I was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Their 
mutual interest would be the mine and their employment? Were there any divisions between craftsmen and labourers amongst the miners would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Not in those days, no. NO. Everything was in the role.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 After Rhodesia, where did you move to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Came home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 When was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Went to Malaya. Spent three years out there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was around the 1930's was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 From '28 to '31. With my wife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you usually do a three year contract in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, that was a three ye
ar's contract, yes. The other one from the Rurh, I actually got fired by - an American engineer here - who took a dislike to me. He was sent out from England and he - he got fired about - oh I had - I had a cable when I was going out to Malaya, from the m
ine saying rejoice with us, the - manager is leaving today. W}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 've drank all the beer in - on the mine, all the beer in An}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 ola, and Vancouver and we've sent to Elizabethville for more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Everybody was very pleased about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes. But I had - I was - a first engineer there and the first engineer to get fired.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was really due to difficulties with the management?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Aye. And - some - six years later they - wired me from - London asking me the same company asking me to go to South Ameri
ca again. South America.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So then you were back in South America, would that be Venezuela again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Yes, but in the meantime I had gone to Canada, when I came home from Malaya. Went out to Canada, and - visited the old spots where I'd been before. And then I had to go in the mill to learn the metal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 urgy of gold, then I had this cable to go down to South }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 America and I went down the And}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 es from there. Down through - five hundred miles down to the - and then across from Niag}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 ra and then up to New York a
nd down to Haiti - San Domingo, and then up the Magdalena River. The first trip was up the Orinoco, four hundred and fifty mile, and - a hundred and eighty mile across country in an old lorry. And no roads or anything. Well this time it was down - into - 
up the Magdalena, up near - Bog}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 ta.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So it was pretty rough travel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 ing in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh terrible travel, yes. Terrible travel. Sixteen hours in the saddle going over the mountains.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was by pony was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pard}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 on? Yes. Going across raging tor}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
rents and - knee deep in mud sometimes and poor - a pony could hardly stand up. Sixteen hours in the saddle that time. I came home again after about eight months. And - then they sent me out to - they says - now, wait a minute, don't run away, the s
election trust wired - cabled me again and asked me to go out to - to Venezuela again. The other time I was away down in Columbia. So - I went down on the border of British Guiana, down through Venezuela on the border of British Guiana, looking for gold a
nd diamonds, and we were - I was unconscious for three days. They bathed my body in - rum, native rum. There was no doctor, no nothing, like that, terrible place. Terrible trip.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That must have been a very rough time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Very rough time. Extremely ro
ugh. Then we - I left there, I was sent by my boss - back to where I was in 1926. To report on some properties there and - it took us twenty-four hours to get over small rapids going up, we - we - went over them by accident, with twenty-three people in a 
dug-out, all women and children. Couldn't stop the boat. Shot over the rapids, if there'd been six inches less water every one would}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 have been drowned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 This would be a steamer would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. A dug-out. Yes. No steamers, not then. Absolutely no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You couldn't get 'em in there anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 This was largely prospecting would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, reporting. Examination and reporting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Surveying and reporting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Examination and reporting on - property, gold properties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So that you wouldn't stay very long in one place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Oh no. Oh no. It was an expedition. I - well it's - there I managed a mine called the McCubrie Gold mines. Then - the - for the same company that I went out for in 1926, they asked me if I would remain behind to manage t
he mine for them for six months while the manager went home. It was very much improved then and I did, I stayed there for six months, I managed the McCopa gold mine, in El Caliog, not Calio, El Caliog. Then when I came home I - the selection trust - sent 
m
e out to - Lake Victoria and Iansa, out in Kenya. I - I went out there to report an open - little gold properties too, there was a bit of a rush out there then, gold rush. So I was on the north shore of Lake Victoria and Ianda, for a year, all over the pl
a
ce, into Uganda and back and so on, Nairobi. Then - then I came back - in '36. And I tried to start a mine up here, Jenner. I was in London and the - office, and they said, would you like to have a job up in Cumberland managing a mine for us Cumberland? S
o I said, yes, I wouldn't mind at all. Well they said, you go up and have a look at it. So we went up to Ullswater, a man called Greenside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It's in the Lake District?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Yes. I was manager up there for a time. Shifted all our furniture from here, this house and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You've been able to take Mrs Harry with you to that sort of assignment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Yes. She was out with me in Malaya. She was out with me in Canada. She was up in Cumberland. She was later out in Siam with me. I had a chance of a better job out there. She was out there with me. We got away just before the Japs came down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was in 1940,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 1930 - 40 - 41. Yes. And we all we left behind were massacred. Aye.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You were fortunate then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Then after Siam that was the second world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Yes, that's right. Yes, we got away from there, I went down South Africa. Well I had a - a commission in the Intelligence Corps - from Singapore. I was supposed to get back to - Singapore and go up on the border, and wh
en war broke out my wife and I were staying at Victoria Falls Hotel, and we - I cabled and everything and did everything possible. And couldn't get any reply until the twelfth of February, and they said regret no vacancy, do not return. Otherwise I would 
have been in the bag with the rest of them. I bought a gold mine of my own in Rhodesia then, Southern Rhodesia.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You went there then did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You went to Southern Rhodesia then did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well - Lake Victoria - the - Victoria Falls are in Southern Rhodesia.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 This intelligence assignment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
I didn't - I - I didn't get it you see because I went to South Africa on a holiday, and they said they'd get me back by the fifteenth of December, and they didn't do it. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So that fell through then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Yes, that was a - but I tried to get back there but it's - a good job I didn't. So I bought this little gold mine - in - of my own in Rhodesia. I had two Dutchmen and seventy-five cutters working for me. Used to get about fifty o
r fifty-four ounces of gold a month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And that was worthwhile?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Oh it was only just. I lost about fifteen hundred pound up there. But my wife didn't like the - life, Saturday night when the - cutters all got drunk and - the tom-toms were going all
 the time, and we - right away out, there was nobody within two miles of us in the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Lonely?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Very - for her, yes. So I - we sold it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 When was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Ay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 How long did you stay up there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 A year I think. A year - a year - abou
t fif - sixteen months altogether. Mm. We spent two or three holidays in Johannesburg, our first one in Durban and then Johannesburg. Then when we sold out in Rhodesia we went down to Johannesburg and then down to Cape Town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And you stayed there then did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
No, we came home on a - boat without an escort - or - doctor or anything, just four passengers. And we went up the coast of Numacwaland and up the Congo river, to Matadi, took on - palm oil. On a little - little Dutch boat called the Print -
 Trent - Prentis, and then we went across the Guld of Guinea to Sierra Leone to Freetown. Then we had - word - we had to pack up quick and get on - a boat which had come from India and North Africa full of convict - prisoners and - women and children and 
a
ll that. Fifteen hundred of 'em. And we had to go up Casablanca and join a convoy. We were in - we were in - Freetown on Christmas Day 1942. And - we were - were in Gourock on the sixteenth of January, we were six and half - six and a half weeks coming ho
me, from Cape Town, floating around the Atlantic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You joined a liner then from Freetown?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Joined a liner with about fifteen hundred on it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 In '42?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Came home on a convoy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And put in at Gourock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You weren't allowed to run risks or anything like that. We landed up in Gourock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So then you were in England from then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Scotland, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you take any more employment then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Any what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you take any more employment then from 1942?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh - I - I 
was - told to sit out alone by the intelligence - were - interrogated by the - British Intelligence when I landed up there, 'cos I'd been in Siam as a - more or less secret agent some time. Then I had to go to the War Office then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 They wanted to know what things were like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
I had to give a lot of information in the War Office. I was in the War Office on the twenty-third of - twenty-third of January. Then I asked to join - train as a paratrooper to blow some bridges in Siam. And then I was offered 
a commission in the Movements Control to go to Normandy when it started. When I got home I had a job - telling me to join the coal - open cast coal board up in Leeds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It was very important then to get all the coal we could?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. And then I did a
 - I had bad lodgings, and I did a tremendous amount of work at night again. And - I got promoted on to take the whole of the north outcrop of the South Wales Coalfield. I had a lot of technical assistants and all that there. So I was with the Coal Board 
for - about two and a half years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So that was to the end of the war I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Yes. And then I was asked to resign to go out with the British Tin Mission to Siam. And I was here in this house for six months waiting to go because of the - amount o
f bandits and that - hold ups and that on the Siamese border. I went away in August '46. Your tape is running you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So you went to Siam in '46?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, I went to Malaya and we weren't allowed into Siam because of this - bandits were still up the
re. Then I went up there in November, in a jeep that I had painted white so the - the bandits would know it wasn't a military jeep, because they killed fourteen - the day before we got up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 How long did you stay in Siam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 The co}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
pany had - erected a very expensive plant to recover tin by the chloridisation method, an electro - an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 electrolyte}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
 - lytic method, and - it was the first of its kind in the world. It involved the erection of a very large amount of machinery to turn the tin into gas, and then conden}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
e it and later on - pass it over some - cells, electrolytic cells - to - where it would be deposited as - metallic tin. These cells were then lifted out and the metallic tin taken off, and - smelted and it was over ninety-nine percent pure. 
But the Siamese had - it had only started about three weeks before the war broke out, and it had a lot of teething troubles, and the Siamese had come down during the war and - do you want me to stop? And stolen - or - or taken away all the power - new pow
e
r plant - five hundred and fifty horse - power electrolytic - electros - electricity station and a hundred and twenty' five motor, and - taken it up to Bangkok when the British and American forces were bombing Bangkok. Apart from that the Siamese - careta
k
ers down there had stolen every piece of - every article of - machinery that would move, especially anything with which they could make knives, like - the - chrome nickel stuff. Anyhow we got in there and found all this mess, and the place overgrown and e
v
erything like that, and - no electricity, no nothing you see. And - went over the mine and estimated this and estimated that, how much it was - going to cost to - make the mine back to production - even after we'd taken it over from Siamese Government, wh
ich didn't happen until July 1948.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That's two years then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Pretty well two years, and I had to go to Bangkok on several occasions, but - one night - when we got up there, we got - we got up there my - clerk came to me and said that the - the - ba
ndit chief had come to see me. And - I was very worried, I asked him what it was all about and he said, oh he's come to welcome you back. You used - you did him a great favour when he was working for you before the war, because I was there before the war 
y
ou see. And he came to welcome me back - he was later shot - as a - a bandit somewhere on the north east corner of - in the north east corner of Malaya. But he told me that he could take any contract I had now, and I asked him where he get all the money a
nd he said, he - kidnapped a - a Toky}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
, that's one of the - Chinese - rich Chinese - headmen, and had twenty-two thousand dollars ransom from him you see. So I told him next time he was going to do it I'd go with him. Anyway, I happened to go to Bangkok in 
a plane and this man was on - on board and they'd tortured him so much he was foaming from the mouth you know, had a man looking after him all the time. Anyhow, we - were up there for three months, two of us. And we didn't get worried by bandits or anythi
ng like that but we had a lot of trouble with the Siamese - official in charge of care}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
taking you know and that sort of thing. V went to Bangkok several times, I met the Prime Minister named Tweedy, and I - I told to go and see an Admiral - Chully, to get these - motors all down, they were in the Siamese Naval Department, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 They knew where they were then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Pardon? Oh yes, yes, I - I - located them you see. And this - Admiral had been educated at Sheffield University. And the next time I went u
p to Bangkok he was in prison because he had kidnapped the Premier or something like that. Anyhow we got the motors all down. And after a lot of this, that the other thing took over the mine in about July - 19 - 48. They had spent over - later spent over 
t
wo hundred thousand pounds on - rehabilitation but - there were a lot of mechanical defects, and - later on the - we produced tin and all this, that and the other thing, but later on they wanted to spend a lot more money and they wrote up and asked me and
 I said in view of the - French surrender in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
ambodia, Pnom Phenn - Pnom Phenn yes, I - wouldn't recommend it. So - in 1954 - 52, the thing was closed down and - I - I quit, well A was in Ireland and I had a cable asking me to go back there. To carry out a 
drilling programme which I recommended. But - they spent no further money there and later on - some Japanese - took it over, and they lost a very large amount of money. Very large amount of money there. Anyhow I retired in '54. I came home in '49 and then
 came home in '52. And I came home in '54.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was a very distinguished career then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Pardon? I don't know so much distinguished, I can see a lot of faults I made. A lot, a great deal, yes. But I was held up - three times, ambushed three times and held up, one time I was looking straight down the muzzle of a gun.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 This was out in India or during the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? No, I - no, no, out - when I was out in Siam. Yes. Because I had to go down to Penang for anything - foodstuff mostly, you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You risked meeting up with the bandits then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh lots and lots of times, lots of times, oh yes, yes. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I suppose a lot of our chaps working there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No, there weren't a lot of our - our chaps working out there at all. No. I only had about half a dozen Europeans altogether. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 During the first war when you are serving you told me that you had been commissioned, I suppose that was commissioned as second L}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 eutenant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, I was made Second - I was - an NCO and we went 
to sleep on - duty one night, through being on so long and I - reverted to the ranks, and then one day - twenty-second of February 19 - 17 I was recommended for a commission in the - in a battle - outside Coot. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was Mesopotamia was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, Mesopotamia,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So then you were commissioned, what rank did you hold when the war was over?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 First L}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
eutenant. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You did mention about the general conditions of the roads when you started to work first down the mine, you were say
ing that they were pretty muddy and it was a job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Oh yes, sure, mud that deep I mean - they were everywhere on a - but Levant - Levant - road where the traction engine came up every day, it was - ter - terrible in the mornings at - half past six goin
g down there in the dark. Terrible, I mean there wasn't a bit dry as big as that that you could walk on properly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Just about a foot of road that you could really walk on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, you - you couldn't walk - that was very very irregular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It must have been pretty eerie for a lad fourteen going off in the dark?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, well it was actually yes. But then lots more went the same you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You would have had some company with other chaps I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh going down the road. No, not necessary, no. Very very seldom, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 How did you feel about going underground as a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I hated it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Did you feel fear at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I hated it down there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You feel awfully closed in and the work would be hard and dirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, I didn't like
 it at all. I wanted to travel, that's the reason I went down there but I - I - would have got out of it if I could. But my parents - parents told me that once having started on my - father when he - was abroad well you'd better stick at it and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It was what all the lads did at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, that's right, yes, ninety - ninety-five out of a hundred I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Actually it was probably far better paid at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Pardon? One and three - one and three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 pence a day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I was interviewing somebody else who was paid four and sixpence a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, well not down in a place like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So that underground with the dangers, you had to submit to those dangers to get anything like a reasonable wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And unpleasantness, and bad 
air and smoke and - heat, it was terrible. I think - I was read - reading my notes this last week, I - I think that - I was in - probably one of the worst places in the mine. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 For air?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Of course - yes, and since - since I've trave}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 led a lot and studied a lot I realize just - how bad conditions were more than ever. You wouldn't be - you wouldn't be allowed to work there today. But you wouldn't get anybody to work there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 They do have to counteract that bad atmosphere now don't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 O
h they've got the - they have - ventilation, there should be, but that depends on the inspector of mines. For instance, in many many places in Geevor right now they're }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 fifty}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912  I understand. But I shouldn't put that on record, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That's where you worked part of the time as a lad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. But even now, I mean, with - ventilation as it is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It ought to be better?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Oh much - much better. A lot of those men killed the other day, about a year ago was killed because he couldn't see where he was going.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Foggy?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Three - three - three ladders. Go away through and then down three ladders. So that if the sea had broken through before - the man engine burst everybody down there in - practically would have been drowned because it - you would have
 to come up part of the way in that shaft.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It was underneath sea level?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, well it wasn't underneath sea level but the - the water would come down through there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And fill up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Aye. Couldn't go up against it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So it was fortunate in a way although lives were lost that the man engine broke?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well - I think so. I think - many times thought since that it was a blessing in disguise. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And the only light you had was a candle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Candle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 This candle was fixed to your helmet was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Usually. Sometimes you took it off or - had it in your hand all depends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 It was pretty grim?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Well if you're born - round in that area and that atmosphere you don't take so much notice of it later. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 I was thinking of starting it as a lad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Oh yes. Yes. I - I think - I think it affects every - youngsters as a - when you first go underground. Yes. Oh I think so. It was unpleasant anyhow and - particularly hot down there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 And of course there's no way out except by clim}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 ing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Yes. And what else could you do, had to either go into a carpenters shop and not many carpenters around, what else was there to do? Farming. Who wanted - farm - didn't want to be a farm labourer. There was no other occupati
on. Gone teaching - I could have gone in for a teacher my father told me if I wanted to, but that wouldn't let me travel.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was the only way out and you certainly took it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Your wife's family were mining as well weren't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Oh everybody, yes. And my - my - mother's people, my father's people. My wife's - maternal and paternal - grandparents and all that sort of thing. Well as I say, her father was in Kimberley in 1888. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 You said about her uncle going across the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Her - her uncle went across Panama, yes. Yes. He was - one time - mine captain of Bassett after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That's Bassett up in the Camborne area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Mrs Harry was a schoolteacher did you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes. Originally. Yes, we were married in Canada. And we came home and her next trip was to Malaya.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 She saw a lot of the world as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
Yes. Yes, and - and then her next trip was to Siam in '38/39. That was when we - we left there fortunately three months before the Japs landed, and went
 down to South Africa, I - I was to go back into the - Army. I got my papers to - to say I was to go back but they would cable me but they didn't cable me. I said, we were in - at Victoria Falls Hotel in - when - the Japs landed out in - Malaya and Siam.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 So you didn't go then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 No. And - she went up to Rhodesia - I bought a small goldmine up ther}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 
e. And she - didn't like the - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 afford when they were drunk on Saturday night, we were away out - on our own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Right in the country?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14942850 WH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 Yes, twenty-five miles from Bulowayo. So I sold up, we went down Johan}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16126770\charrsid13072912 n}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 
esburg then we went down to Cape Town. And came home, went up the Congo River and all - to Freetown. We were six and a half weeks out on the - out on the Congo - out on the - Atlantic floating about.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5595290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077243\charrsid13072912 That was during the war?
